---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Requirements & Equipment | MCM Amateur Radio Operations"
  description="Licensing, equipment, and preparation requirements for MCM Amateur Radio Operations volunteers."
>
  <div class="py-12">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <Icon name="lucide:award" class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto text-[#CC0000] mb-4" aria-hidden="true" />
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Requirements & Equipment</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Everything you need to know about licensing, equipment, and preparation for volunteering as an amateur
          radio operator at the Marine Corps Marathon.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">License Requirements</h2>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200">
          <div class="flex gap-4 mb-4">
            <Icon name="lucide:award" class="w-8 h-8 text-[#CC0000] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Valid FCC Amateur Radio License</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                All volunteers must hold a current, valid FCC amateur radio license. We accept all license classes:
              </p>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Technician Class</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Entry-level license with VHF/UHF privileges</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">General Class</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Intermediate license with expanded HF access</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Amateur Extra</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Highest license class with full privileges</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-4 bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                  <strong>Don't have your license yet?</strong> Visit{' '}
                  <a
                    href="https://www.arrl.org/getting-licensed"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="text-blue-700 underline">ARRL's Getting Licensed page</a
                  >
                  to find exam sessions near you. Once you pass, we'd love to have you on our team!
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Equipment Requirements</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <Icon name="lucide:circle-check" class="w-6 h-6 text-green-600" aria-hidden="true" />
              <h3 class="font-bold text-xl">Required Equipment</h3>
            </div>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <Icon name="lucide:radio" class="w-5 h-5 text-[#CC0000] shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
                <div>
                  <strong>VHF/UHF Radio:</strong> A dual-band VHF/UHF (2m/70cm) handheld (HT) tranceiver capable of 2-meter and 70-centimeter operation
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <Icon name="lucide:battery" class="w-5 h-5 text-[#CC0000] shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
                <div>
                  <strong>Power:</strong> Fresh batteries or fully charged battery pack (plan for 6-12 hours of
                  operation)
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <Icon name="lucide:headphones" class="w-5 h-5 text-[#CC0000] shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
                <div>
                  <strong>Audio Accessory:</strong> Earpiece or speaker mic recommended for noisy environments
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <Icon name="lucide:circle-check" class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" aria-hidden="true" />
              <h3 class="font-bold text-xl">Recommended Equipment</h3>
            </div>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <Icon name="lucide:battery" class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600 shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
                <div>
                  <strong>Spare Batteries:</strong> Extra battery pack or AA battery case
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <Icon name="lucide:radio" class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600 shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
                <div>
                  <strong>Dual-Band Radio:</strong> 2m/70cm capability provides flexibility
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <Icon name="lucide:headphones" class="w-5 h-5 text-blue-600 shrink-0 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true" />
                <div>
                  <strong>VOX Headset:</strong> Hands-free operation for roving positions
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Popular Radio Models Used by Our Team</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            While any VHF-capable radio will work, here are some models commonly used by our operators:
          </p>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-sm">
            <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded border border-gray-200">
              <strong>Yaesu FT-60R</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Rugged dual-band HT</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded border border-gray-200">
              <strong>Baofeng UV-5R</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Budget-friendly option</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded border border-gray-200">
              <strong>Kenwood TH-D74A</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Advanced features</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded border border-gray-200">
              <strong>Icom ID-52A</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600">D-STAR capable</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Personal Items to Bring</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <Icon name="lucide:shirt" class="w-8 h-8 text-[#CC0000] mb-4" aria-hidden="true" />
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Clothing & Comfort</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
              <li>• Weather-appropriate clothing (check forecast)</li>
              <li>• Comfortable shoes (you may be standing for hours)</li>
              <li>• Hat and sunglasses for outdoor positions</li>
              <li>• Rain gear if weather threatens</li>
              <li>• Layers (temperature can change throughout the day)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <Icon name="lucide:clock" class="w-8 h-8 text-[#CC0000] mb-4" aria-hidden="true" />
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Essentials</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
              <li>• Water bottle (stay hydrated!)</li>
              <li>• Snacks or lunch</li>
              <li>• Notepad and pen for logging</li>
              <li>• Watch or clock for time checks</li>
              <li>• Fully charged cell phone</li>
              <li>• Portable chair (if assigned to stationary position)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Logistics & Availability</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#CC0000]">
            <Icon name="lucide:clock" class="w-8 h-8 text-[#CC0000] mb-4" aria-hidden="true" />
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Time Commitment</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Plan to be available for the entire race day, typically:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
              <li>• <strong>Check-in:</strong> 6:00 AM - 6:30 AM</li>
              <li>• <strong>On-position:</strong> 7:00 AM - 3:00 PM</li>
              <li>• <strong>Debrief:</strong> 3:00 PM - 3:30 PM</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">Total commitment: Approximately 9-10 hours</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#CC0000]">
            <Icon name="lucide:car" class="w-8 h-8 text-[#CC0000] mb-4" aria-hidden="true" />
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Transportation & Parking</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Important logistics information:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
              <li>• Parking information provided with assignment</li>
              <li>• Some positions require personal vehicle for roving</li>
              <li>• Public transportation options available</li>
              <li>• Rideshare to/from venue encouraged</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#CC0000] to-[#8B0000] text-white rounded-lg p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Preparation Tips</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Before Race Day</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90">
              <li>✓ Test your radio and confirm it's working properly</li>
              <li>✓ Charge all batteries fully</li>
              <li>✓ Program frequencies (we'll provide list)</li>
              <li>✓ Review race course map and your assignment</li>
              <li>✓ Attend the pre-race briefing (mandatory)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Race Day Morning</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90">
              <li>✓ Arrive early for check-in</li>
              <li>✓ Verify radio operation on test frequency</li>
              <li>✓ Get assignment details and position map</li>
              <li>✓ Understand your reporting chain</li>
              <li>✓ Know the emergency procedures</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
